This lab requires 2 Linux machines.
Put both machines network card in NAT mode. Remove manual IP address and put it on DHCP.
If iptables is installed then stop iptables service. Disable it. Unmask the firewalld service.
Enable firewalld service and start the firewalld service. 
Set hostname to both the machines - server and client1 

Now follow the OSSEC server installation steps.

Once the OSSEC server is installed then install OSSEC client on the second machine.


OSSEC HIDS Lab Setup (Server + Client)
Lab Topology
Machine
Hostname
Role
Machine 1
server
OSSEC Manager
Machine 2
client1
OSSEC Agent

Both machines should be in NAT Network mode and obtain IP addresses via DHCP.

Step 1: Configure Both Machines
Verify Network Adapter
In VMware/VirtualBox:
Select VM
Network Adapter → NAT
Save settings

Remove Static IP and Enable DHCP
Check Interface Name
ip a

Example interface:
ens33


Edit Network Configuration
For Rocky Linux / CentOS:
sudo nmcli con show

Find connection name and configure DHCP:
sudo nmcli con mod ens33 ipv4.method auto
sudo nmcli con up ens33

Verify:
ip a


Disable iptables (If Installed)
Check:
systemctl status iptables

Stop:
sudo systemctl stop iptables

Disable:
sudo systemctl disable iptables


Unmask Firewalld
sudo systemctl unmask firewalld


Enable and Start Firewalld
sudo systemctl enable firewalld
sudo systemctl start firewalld

Verify:
systemctl status firewalld


Step 2: Configure Hostnames
On Server Machine
sudo hostnamectl set-hostname server

Verify:
hostname

Output:
server


On Client Machine
sudo hostnamectl set-hostname client1

Verify:
hostname

Output:
client1


Step 3: Update Both Systems
sudo dnf update -y

or
sudo yum update -y


Step 4: Install OSSEC Server (Manager)
Perform these steps on server machine.

Install Required Packages
sudo dnf install wget gcc gcc-c++ make unzip tar inotify-tools -y


Download OSSEC
cd /tmp

wget https://github.com/ossec/ossec-hids/archive/3.7.0.tar.gz

Extract:
tar -xzf 3.7.0.tar.gz

Move:
cd ossec-hids-3.7.0


Start Installation
sudo ./install.sh


Installation Answers
Choose:
English

Press Enter
What kind of installation?

Enter:
server


Enable Features
Answer:
Integrity check daemon?      y
Rootkit detection?           y
Active response?             y
Firewall response?           y


Finish installation.
Expected path:
/var/ossec


Start OSSEC
sudo /var/ossec/bin/ossec-control start

Check:
sudo /var/ossec/bin/ossec-control status


Step 5: Allow OSSEC Port
OSSEC uses UDP 1514.
Open firewall:
sudo firewall-cmd --permanent --add-port=1514/udp

Reload:
sudo firewall-cmd --reload

Verify:
sudo firewall-cmd --list-ports

Expected:
1514/udp


Step 6: Create Agent on Server
Launch Agent Manager:
sudo /var/ossec/bin/manage_agents


Menu:
(A) Add agent
(E) Extract key
(Q) Quit


Add Agent
Choose:
A

Agent Name:
client1

IP Address:
<Client IP>

Example:
192.168.122.102

ID:
001


Extract Key
Choose:
E

Select:
001

Copy the generated key.
Example:
MDAxIGNsaWVudDEgMTkyLjE2OC4x...

Save it.

Step 7: Install OSSEC Agent
Perform on client1 machine.

Install Dependencies
sudo dnf install wget gcc gcc-c++ make unzip tar inotify-tools -y


Download OSSEC
cd /tmp

wget https://github.com/ossec/ossec-hids/archive/3.7.0.tar.gz

Extract:
tar -xzf 3.7.0.tar.gz

cd ossec-hids-3.7.0


Start Installation
sudo ./install.sh


Installation Type
Select:
agent


Manager IP
Enter:
<Server IP>

Example:
192.168.122.101


Finish installation.

Step 8: Import Agent Key
Run:
sudo /var/ossec/bin/manage_agents

Choose:
I

Paste copied key.
Press:
Q


Step 9: Start Agent
sudo /var/ossec/bin/ossec-control start

Verify:
sudo /var/ossec/bin/ossec-control status


Step 10: Verify Communication
On Server:
sudo /var/ossec/bin/agent_control -l

Expected:
OSSEC HIDS agent_list.

ID: 001, Name: client1, IP: 192.168.x.x, Active


Step 11: Generate Test Alert
On Client:
sudo su -

echo "failed login test" >> /var/log/secure

Or:
sudo su -
cat /etc/shadow


Step 12: Check Alerts on Server
sudo tail -f /var/ossec/logs/alerts/alerts.log

You should see alerts arriving from:
client1


Useful OSSEC Commands
Server Status
sudo /var/ossec/bin/ossec-control status

Agent List
sudo /var/ossec/bin/agent_control -l

Restart OSSEC
sudo /var/ossec/bin/ossec-control restart

Real-Time Alerts
sudo tail -f /var/ossec/logs/alerts/alerts.log

Stop OSSEC
sudo /var/ossec/bin/ossec-control stop

At the end of the lab, verify:
Both machines obtain IP via DHCP.
Hostnames are server and client1.
Firewalld is running.
OSSEC manager is running on server.
OSSEC agent is running on client1.
agent_control -l shows the client as Active.

